10  // Chebyshev polynomials of the first kind

12  /**
13  * Return the Chebyshev polynomial of the first kind @f$ T_n(x) @f$
14  * of non-negative order @c n and real argument @c x.
15  *
16  * The Chebyshev polynomial of the first kind is defined by:
17  * @f[
18  * T_n(x) = \cos(n \theta)
19  * @f]
20  * where @f$ \theta = \arccos(x) @f$, @f$ -1 <= x <= +1 @f$.
21  *
22  * @tparam Tp The real type of the argument
23  * @param n The non-negative integral order
24  * @param x The real argument @f$ -1 <= x <= +1 @f$
25  */
26  template<typename Tp>
27  inline emsr::fp_promote_t<Tp>
28  chebyshev_t(unsigned int n, Tp x)
29  {
30  using type = emsr::fp_promote_t<Tp>;
31  return emsr::detail::chebyshev_t<type>(n, x).T_n;
32  }

34  // Chebyshev polynomials of the second kind

36  /**
37  * Return the Chebyshev polynomial of the second kind @f$ U_n(x) @f$
38  * of non-negative order @c n and real argument @c x.
39  *
40  * The Chebyshev polynomial of the second kind is defined by:
41  * @f[
42  * U_n(x) = \frac{\sin \left[(n+1)\theta \right]}{\sin(\theta)}
43  * @f]
44  * where @f$ \theta = \arccos(x) @f$, @f$ -1 <= x <= +1 @f$.
45  *
46  * @tparam Tp The real type of the argument
47  * @param n The non-negative integral order
48  * @param x The real argument @f$ -1 <= x <= +1 @f$
49  */

60  /**
61  * Return the Chebyshev polynomial of the third kind @f$ V_n(x) @f$
62  * of non-negative order @c n and real argument @c x.
63  *
64  * The Chebyshev polynomial of the third kind is defined by:
65  * @f[
66  * V_n(x) = \frac{\cos \left[ \left(n+\frac{1}{2}\right)\theta \right]}
67  * {\cos \left(\frac{\theta}{2}\right)}
68  * @f]
69  * where @f$ \theta = \arccos(x) @f$, @f$ -1 <= x <= +1 @f$.
70  *
71  * @tparam Tp The real type of the argument

73  * @param x The real argument @f$ -1 <= x <= +1 @f$
